  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Supporting small-scale fishers build thriving and resilient livelihoods, Bonthe District</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Summary of Significant Change
- Improved access to marine resources for both men and women through community parctipation in management processes
- increased household incomes for smallscale fishers/prcocessors through access to improved equipment and fishsmokers
- reduced incidence of ailments due to excessive smoke inhalation by women during fish processing
- reduction in fish spoilage due to access to solar cold storage facilities and hence improved access to fresh fish markets for increased incomes
- reduction in household expenditure on fossil fuel energy sources as result of introduction of solar lighting products
-</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main project activities to be implemented by MCSL, EJF, EFO and HAGDI (local CBO), will be as follows:
 - Formation of 15 fishing groups (comprising 225 men and 225 women) 
 - Groups provided with improved fishing equipment, fish smokers, training and linked to Government agencies/ministries. 
-  Provide 5 solar-powered Community Cold Storage Stations (CCSS) 
 - Beekeeping will be a new income-generating activity for the area 
 - Training in sustainable techniques for harvesting the oysters from the mangrove forests.
 - Facilitate collaboration with District Council, Community Management Association and Ministry of Marine Resources and 
 community meetings, engagement and learning events on sustainable fishing, 
 - Monitoring and reporting of IUU (using modern equipment)
 - Promotion of collaborative community management of marine resources</narrative>
  </description>
